Item ID5290

A calquat tree seed can only be planted in a filled plant pot. After watering the calquat seedling it will grow into a calquat sapling, which may then be planted in the calquat patch in Tai Bwo Wannai (72 Farming) to grow into a calquat tree. When fully grown, calquat fruits may be harvested.

Once grown, players can harvest a maximum of 6 calquat fruits at a time. If the player does not dig up the tree, more fruits will grow eventually.

A fully grown calquat tree will give a total of 12,516.5 experience, with 129.5 experience for planting, 12,096 experience for checking and 291 experience for harvesting 6 fruit.

The nearby gardener Imiago will watch over your growing calquat tree at the cost of a payment of 8 poison ivy berries. No quest is needed to use the calquat patch or for paying the gardener.

Many players find that these seeds are one of the best in the game, because of their high checking experience and very low cost compared to other tree seeds around their level. However, there is only one calquat patch in the game. The calquat farming patch can be cleared by using a spade on the stump.

Calquat tree seeds can be found in bird nests.
